```

Example output files:

```text
figures/sdm_impacts_SocioEconomic_Building.png
figures/sdm_impacts_LandscapeMetrics.png
```

---

## Output folder

The script automatically creates:

```text
figures/
```

All generated figures are stored here.

---

## Dependencies

Required Python packages:

```text
pandas
numpy
matplotlib
seaborn
openpyxl
```

---

## Workflow order

This script depends on outputs generated from:

```text
energy.py
landscape.py
analysis_OLS.py
SDM analysis
```

Recommended order:

1. energy processing
2. landscape metrics processing
3. regression analysis
4. SDM modelling
5. figure generation

---

## How to run

From the project root directory:

```bash
python analysis/figure.py
```

Or:

```bash
python figure.py
```

---

## Notes

The script automatically skips missing variables or missing input files.

Violin plots remove outliers within each urbanity group using the standard 1.5×IQR rule.

SDM significance is detected automatically from asterisk-marked coefficients in the Excel file.
